Yes, the print command only can show 8K characters, that&#039;s why we used looping in the code to get 8000 characters to print then next 8000.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Adam&#039;s bcp trick seems to be the simplest way of getting all procedure codes into a file.

If the procedure size is longer than 8K result of PRINT will be truncated in Management Studio, regardless of any settings I could find, even if you are using varchar(max). &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
If you execute it via sqlcmd you get everything and you don&#039;t need Print @var(Left,8000).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It seems print command can print only 8k strings inside studio while it works fine in sqlcmd.
